{"url": "https://www.thirtyminded.com/home/style/best-jean-shorts-for-your-figure", "text": "Jean Shorts with Stretch\n\nSlender figure\n\nYes, go for it! This style is great because if you don\u2019t have big hips to keep your shorts up, you have the spandex/stretch element working for you. Also without wide hips you don\u2019t have a lot of extra inner thigh to go around so it won\u2019t look weird when it hugs you there. You can rock these and we are all jealous!\n\nStraight figure\n\nNo matter what you weigh, this figure has a waist bust and hip measurement that are all pretty similar and this style of jean shorts would work really well for your figure. Like the slender body style, the stretch will keep your shorts in place!\n\nPear / Hourglass or \u201cSmall Waist with a Big \u2018Ol Booty\u201d\n\nPear/Hourglass: Both are the same when it comes to shorts unless we are comparing a normal human with a supermodel. Supermodels you can wear anything. So I\u2019m going with an hourglass or pear figure human when it comes to this advice.\n\nThis is me (the NON super model option), so trust me with this.. I\u2019ve tried everything. Here\u2019s what I have found: AVOID ANYTHING WITH SPANDEX! Stretch denim shorts do not look good on this body style in my opinion. If you want a saggy butt or your inner thighs to look like they\u2019re grasping for air then sure, go for it. Otherwise, go for denim that lacks elasticity.", "images": ["https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5a4e55718dd041365e9ec461/1532556058177-G9DGYWCYCH3EDK7SZ3N5/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kHem505q6McQd8XRhQc9zkRZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWQUxwkmyExglNqGp0IvTJZUJFbgE-7XRK3dMEBRBhUpxpEURhgSBEh9ILe0HKIG3CcOCklsxWwam3CdWF6Xw7jwVv5P97BEtB5XaVnmvMtTA/image-asset.jpeg", "https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5a4e55718dd041365e9ec461/1522021891071-R7RYS2KSCSB4MQG0YLF2/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kDiLxZttbyc7kxp0qoApdttZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWEtT5uBSRWt4vQZAgTJucoTqqXjS3CfNDSuuf31e0tVEmk_XPFb0QLIV00cPLesSzUiTEmWSxGDYQIG_